-downhill-bike-vhpp-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114234/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-vhpp-800x532.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114234/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-vhpp-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114234/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-vhpp-768x511.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114234/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-vhpp-696x463.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114234/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-vhpp-1068x710.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114234/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-vhpp-632x420.jpg 632w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-261835\">Two links actuate the shock on the Commencal Supreme DH Prototype</figcaption></figure><p>There is a lot to get your head around here. And, without non-driveside images of the suspension linkage, we can do little more than guess at what exactly lies behind the CNC machined plate supporting the chain idler. But, we can tell you there are at least three sets of pivot bearings nestled in behind there.</p><figure id=\"attachment_261836\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-261836\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114243/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-virtual-high-pivot.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114243/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-virtual-high-pivot.jpg\" alt=\"commencal supreme sh prototype\" width=\