3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114243/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-virtual-high-pivot-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114243/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-virtual-high-pivot-800x532.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114243/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-virtual-high-pivot-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114243/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-virtual-high-pivot-768x511.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114243/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-virtual-high-pivot-696x463.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114243/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-virtual-high-pivot-1068x710.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14114243/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-downhill-bike-virtual-high-pivot-632x420.jpg 632w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-261836\">The seat stay brace is the only part of the bike completely under wraps, indicating the possibility of some new technology that actually will reach a production frame in future.</figcaption></figure><p>Connecting that triad of pivots to the rocker is a CNC machined brace plate that has two options for the upper mount. These change the position of the virtual pivot point and also alter the leverage curve; this allows Commencal and their riders to experiment with different setups quickly using the same parts.</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115248/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-rear-dropout-5-speed.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\