bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115248/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-rear-dropout-5-speed.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115248/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-rear-dropout-5-speed-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115248/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-rear-dropout-5-speed-800x532.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115248/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-rear-dropout-5-speed-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115248/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-rear-dropout-5-speed-768x511.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115248/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-rear-dropout-5-speed-696x463.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115248/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-rear-dropout-5-speed-1068x710.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115248/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-rear-dropout-5-speed-632x420.jpg 632w\"></a></p><p>This is not the only point at which adjustments can be made. We asked Commencal about the possibility of chainstay length adjustment. Arthur Quet of the R&amp;D department replied “<em>we have quite a big range, and we also use have a specific rear triangle for Myriam Nicole as she rides the small size frame. Then we can try to figure out what is the best choice testing on different tracks and conditions”</em>.</p><p>The chainring is also hiding a flip-chip at the lower shock mount which Quet tells us allows for no fewer than six mounting options.&nbsp;</p><p><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces.jpg\" alt=\"commencal supreme dh chain idler fixed position\" width=\"1200\" height=\"798\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-800x532.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-768x511.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-696x463.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-1068x710.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-632x420.jpg 632w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb18 src ng ngcb18 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-800x532.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-768x511.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-696x463.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-1068x710.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14115611/supreme-dh-commencal-chain-idler-isolate-chain-forces-632x420.jpg 632w\"></a></p><p>Welded to the base of the seat tube, just above what might normally be considered the “main pivot” (sitting just behind the chain ring), is the aluminium plate that supports the chain idler. On the current production <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/07/02/commencal-supreme-mullet-downhill-bike-lets-amaury-pierron-do-the-talking/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Supreme</a>, the idler’s position changes as the bike goes through its rear wheel travel as it is bolted to the rear swingarm.</p><p>However, on the prototype we see here its position does not change as the bike goes through its travel. Here, it is largely responsible for isolating drivetrain forces from the suspension in a bid to reduce, or even eradicate, <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/2020/09/18/aasq-85-what-is-pedal-kick-back-full-suspension-chain-growth/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">pedal kickback</a>.</p><figure id=\"attachment_261839\" aria-describedby=\"caption-attachment-261839\"><a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-suspension.jpg\"><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-suspension.jpg\" alt=\"commencal supreme dh proto\" width=\"1200\" height=\"798\" data-ezsrcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-suspension.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-suspension-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-suspension-800x532.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-suspension-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-suspension-768x511.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-suspension-696x463.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-suspension-1068x710.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-suspension-632x420.jpg 632w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 1200px) 100vw, 1200px\" ezimgfmt=\"rs rscb18 src ng ngcb18 srcset\" data-ezsrc=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-suspension.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-suspension.jpg 1200w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-suspension-297x198.jpg 297w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-suspension-800x532.jpg 800w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-suspension-120x80.jpg 120w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-suspension-768x511.jpg 768w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-suspension-696x463.jpg 696w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-suspension-1068x710.jpg 1068w,https://bikerumor.com/ezoimgfmt/s3.amazonaws.com/www.bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/14120829/commencal-supreme-dh-prototype-vrtual-high-pivot-point-suspension-632x420.jpg 632w\"></a><figcaption id=\"caption-attachment-261839\">The prototype’s virtual high pivot point likely gives rise to a rearward axle path</figcaption></figure><p>We also asked Arthur Quet for info on the future availability of this bike… <em>“This version of the bike will never go for production. For sure it helps to work on the future Commencal frames but that’s not a sample of upcoming mass production. That’s why all the frame parts are full CNC”</em>.</p><p><a href=\"https://www.commencalusa.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\"><em>CommencalUSA.com</em></a></p></div></div>","author":"Jessie-May Morgan","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"59d20db6ecd576342568b7f73e1197ba27afab34af32fb30bead43bc6877c06c","category":"Cycling"}